## 6. Color Rules

### 6.1 DO:
- ✅ Use CSS variables for theme colors (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`)
- ✅ Use service color palette for service-specific UI
- ✅ Use status colors from the centralized map
- ✅ Support dark mode with `.dark` class overrides
- ✅ Use `hsl()` format for flexibility

### 6.2 DON'T:
- ❌ Use hardcoded hex colors (`#FFD700`)
- ❌ Use Tailwind colors directly (`bg-blue-500`) for brand colors
- ❌ Create one-off color variables
- ❌ Mix color systems inconsistently
- ❌ Ignore dark mode compatibility

